JOHANNESBURG – The ANC in Gauteng will hold its  Provincial General Council (PGC) meeting on Friday. WATCH: ANC's second-biggest province heads to PGC The province will nominate its preferred candidate for ANC president on Saturday. However, speculation is rife that the province will pick Deputy President, Cyril Ramaphosa. The ANC's second biggest province in terms of membership numbers, Mpumalanga held its own PGC. North West province also held its PGC. eNCA